import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['rate'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    ax.set_title('What is the overall trend of unemployment rate across all industries?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.groupby(['series'])['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by=['rate'], ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['series'], data['rate'], color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=data['rate'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['rate'].max():.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Industry')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Unemployment Rate')
    ax.set_title('Which industry has the highest average unemployment rate?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['rate'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['rate'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month_year'] = data['date'].dt.to_period('M')
    data = data.groupby('month_year').mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['month_year'], data['rate'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Month-Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    ax.set_title('How does the unemployment rate vary by month across all industries?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['count'], data['rate'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', label='Median Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].median()))
    ax.axhline(data['rate'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', label='Median Rate: {:.2f}'.format(data['rate'].median()))
    ax.set_xlabel('Count')
    ax.set_ylabel('Rate')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between the number of unemployed individuals and the unemployment rate?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
